# React Architecture Structure

Always follow this structure in `src`:

- `src/pages/<PageName>/<PageName>.tsx`
- `src/pages/<PageName>/<PageName>.css`
- `src/components/<ComponentName>/<ComponentName>.tsx`
- `src/components/<ComponentName>/<ComponentName>.css`

Rules:

- Use PascalCase for folder and file names in pages/components
- Never create files directly under `src/pages/` or `src/components/`
- Create both `.tsx` and `.css` for each new page or component
